From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:19:48 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): journal snapshots with crash-safe compaction
 (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bound recovery-journal growth and replay cost by adding state snapshots to
journal.jsonl plus a crash-safe compaction that truncates the replay prefix
without weakening the FR-E69 durability contract.

- types: add `state_snapshot` event kind / `StateSnapshotJournalEvent`
  (snapshot_version, events_covered, full replayed model) and
  `journal_compaction_threshold_events` to WorkflowDefaults.
- run-journal: extend the SINGLE replayer — parseJournal scans BACKWARD to the
  latest valid snapshot and parses only the suffix (pre-snapshot history never
  read); applyJournalEvents seeds from the snapshot model. Unsupported
  snapshot_version fails replay naming path + version; torn-tail tolerance
  preserved (incl. right after a snapshot). compactJournal runs the exact
  protocol replay -> tmp(one snapshot, zero tail) -> fsync -> .bak(from current
  journal) -> atomic rename, with a per-step faultHook; previewCompaction powers
  --dry-run. One .bak generation kept.
- engine: maybeAutoCompact at executeLevel (node-completion) boundaries only,
  when eventsSinceSnapshot() exceeds the threshold (0 disables); re-opens the
  writer and emits a single verbose line. Engine path bypasses the active-lock
  refusal as the legitimate lock holder.
- mcp/cli: `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <id> [--dry-run]`
  with refuse-before-write on active run / unreplayable journal, exact success
  summary line, non-zero one-line refusals, and --help entry.
- config: validate threshold as a non-negative integer (0 allowed), default 1000.
- docs: register FR-E83 (SRS 01-execution-model, index, requirements map),
  update the engine design journal/recovery section, document the new default in
  README. Compacted adjacent design notes to stay within the per-file token
  budget (facts preserved).
- tests: journal-compaction_test.ts plus config/engine/cli coverage for all 15
  MUST behaviors (suffix-only fixture, snapshot+tail equivalence, crash
  injection at every step). `deno task check` green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
