+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal Snapshots & Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** The recovery journal (`journal.jsonl`, FR-E69) gains a
+  `state_snapshot` event and a crash-safe compaction operation that bounds its
+  growth and replay cost WITHOUT weakening the durability contract.
+
+  **Snapshot event:** a `state_snapshot` record carries `snapshot_version: 1`,
+  the complete replayed run model at that point (everything FR-E69 replay
+  reconstructs — run status/metadata, per-node statuses and facts, declared
+  nodes, costs), and `events_covered` (count of events subsumed).
+
+  **Replay (single replayer, FR-E69's `run-journal.ts`, extended — not
+  forked):** journals without any snapshot replay exactly as before (zero
+  behaviour change). When snapshots are present, replay seeds from the LATEST
+  valid snapshot and applies only events after it; pre-snapshot lines are never
+  parsed. A `snapshot_version` greater than supported fails replay with an error
+  naming the journal path and the unsupported version (no silent skip). The
+  torn-final-line tolerance keeps working on compacted journals, including a
+  torn line immediately after the snapshot. Equivalence: `snapshot + tail`
+  replay reconstructs a run model byte-equal to replaying the full journal.
+
+  **Compaction protocol (shared by engine + CLI), in this exact order:**
+  (1) replay the current journal; (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp` with one
+  `state_snapshot` and zero tail events; (3) fsync tmp; (4) copy the journal to
+  `journal.jsonl.bak`; (5) atomically rename tmp over `journal.jsonl`. A crash
+  at any intermediate point leaves a journal that replays (old or new content,
+  never neither). Exactly one `.bak` generation is kept. Manual compaction
+  refuses (nothing modified) when the run is active (lock held by a live
+  process) or the journal does not replay cleanly beyond torn-line tolerance.
+
+  **Engine integration:** settings field `journal_compaction_threshold_events`
+  (non-negative integer; `0` disables; default `1000`) triggers automatic
+  compaction at node-completion boundaries ONLY (never mid-node) once the events
+  since the last snapshot exceed the threshold; the trigger is one verbose line.
+
+  **CLI:** `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+  [--dry-run]` performs manual compaction with the same protocol/refusals;
+  `--dry-run` previews counts/sizes and writes nothing; success prints exactly
+  `compacted <runId>: <eventsBefore> -> <eventsAfter> events, <bytesBefore> ->
+  <bytesAfter> bytes (backup: journal.jsonl.bak)`; refusals exit non-zero with a
+  one-line error (no stack trace).
+- **Tasks:** [journal-snapshots-compaction](../tasks/2026/06/journal-snapshots-compaction.md)
+- **Motivation:** FR-E69 made replay linear in journal size and deferred
+  compaction; long runs grow `journal.jsonl` unbounded. Snapshots truncate the
+  replay prefix; the crash-safe protocol preserves the recovery contract at
+  every step.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `journal-compaction_test.ts`, `config_test.ts`, `engine_test.ts`,
+    `cli_test.ts` (FR-E83; regression-locked; snapshot format, backward compat,
+    forward refusal, snapshot+tail equivalence, suffix-only replay, torn line
+    after snapshot, every crash-injection point, one-generation backup, both
+    refusal cases, threshold validation + drift, boundary-only auto-trigger,
+    `--dry-run` no-op + exact summary line, `--help` listing).
+
