+# engine: Journal snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Bound the growth of the append-only recovery journal (`journal.jsonl`) and its
+replay cost by adding **state snapshots** to the journal format and a
+**crash-safe compaction** operation — automatic in the engine at node-completion
+boundaries and manual via a new CLI subcommand — that truncates the replay prefix
+WITHOUT ever weakening the FR-E69 durability contract.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 ([durable-run-lifecycle-replay](../05/durable-run-lifecycle-replay.md))
+made `journal.jsonl` the single recovery surface: replay starts from an empty
+in-memory model and applies every event in `seq` order. That task explicitly
+deferred snapshots/compaction ("Snapshot files, embedded snapshot events,
+checkpoint directories, and compaction are not part of the design unless a
+future task demonstrates a measured need."). Long runs now demonstrate that
+need: the journal grows unbounded and replay is linear in journal size.
+
+This task adds an in-journal `state_snapshot` event that subsumes a replay
+prefix, extends the EXISTING replayer (`src/state/run-journal.ts`) to seed from
+the latest snapshot and parse only the suffix, and adds a crash-safe compaction
+protocol shared by the engine (automatic) and CLI (manual).
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns the replay truth: `parseJournal` (line-parse +
+  torn-tail tolerance), `applyJournalEvents` (event→`RunState` fold),
+  `replayRunJournal` (dedupe + apply), `RunJournalWriter` (append-only writer
+  continuing after valid records on resume).
+- `RunJournalEventKind` / `RunJournalEvent` union in `src/types.ts` enumerate
+  the event kinds; every line carries the `RunJournalEventBase` envelope
+  (`schema_version`, `run_id`, `seq`, `event_id`, `kind`, `ts`).
+- The engine (`src/engine/engine.ts`) opens the writer at
+  `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)` (repo-root, OUTSIDE the ephemeral worktree),
+  emits bootstrap facts, and appends node lifecycle facts via
+  `node-lifecycle.ts`. Node completion runs through `Engine.nodeCompleted`;
+  levels execute in `executeLevel` (the only point at which NO node is
+  mid-execution).
+- Workflow-level settings live in `defaults:` (`WorkflowDefaults`, e.g.
+  `max_parallel`); per-field validation sits in `config.ts::validateSchema`
+  (e.g. `validateWallClockBudget`, `validateBudget`). FR-E7 "config drift
+  detection" is exercised by `config_test.ts`.
+- The CLI (`src/cli.ts`) dispatches `run` / `init` / `answer` / `mcp`; the
+  shared command core lives in `src/mcp/commands.ts` (`resumeRun`,
+  `deliverHumanAnswer`); `lock.ts::isRunLive` reports whether a run's lock is
+  held by a live process.
+- Docs: SRS index `documents/requirements-engine.md` + section files;
+  journal/recovery contract documented in `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md`
+  ("Durable Lifecycle Replay (FR-E69)" + the Run Journal entity).
+
+### Constraints
+
+- The EXISTING replayer is the single source of replay truth — extend it; a
+  second replayer is forbidden (req item 4).
+- Backward compatibility: snapshot-free journals replay byte-for-byte as before
+  (req item 2).
+- Suffix-only: replay of a compacted journal MUST NOT parse pre-snapshot lines
+  (req item 7); torn-trailing-line tolerance keeps working, including a torn
+  line immediately after the snapshot (req item 8).
+- Exact crash-safe protocol order (req item 9); a crash at every intermediate
+  point leaves a replayable journal (req item 10).
+- Follow the existing arg-parsing style in `src/cli.ts`; no new dependencies;
+  reuse existing journal-path / state helpers — no duplicated path construction.
+- `deno task check` stays green. Tests live alongside the subsystems they cover.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] FR-E83: Add `state_snapshot` journal event kind whose payload carries
+      `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete replayed run model, and
+      `events_covered`. Test:
+      `journal-compaction_test.ts::FR-E83 snapshot event carries version, model and events_covered`
